quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  12,53,"I do not say my self was free from blame. The self indeed commands to evil acts — except for those my Lord has mercy on. My Lord, He is Forgiving, Merciful.´"
  12,54,"The King said, ´Bring him to me straight away! so I may draw him very close to me.´ When he had spoken with him, he declared, ´Today you are trusted, established in our sight.´"
  12,55,"He said, ´Entrust the country´s stores to me. In truth I am a knowing guardian.´"
  12,56,And thus We established Yusuf in the land so he could live in any place he pleased. We grant Our grace to anyone We will and We do not allow to go to waste the wage of any people who do good
  12,57,But the wages of the akhira are the best for people who have iman and fear their Lord
  12,58,The brothers of Yusuf came into his presence and he knew them but they did not know him
  12,59,"Then, having supplied their needs, he said to them, ´Bring me your brother, your father´s youngest son. Do you not see that I dispense full measure and am the most hospitable of hosts"
  12,60,"But if you do not bring him here to me, your measure from me then will be denied and you will not come near to me at all.´"
  12,61,"They said, ´We will request our father for him. That is something we will surely do.´"
  12,62,"He told his serving men, ´Put back their goods into their saddlebags for them to find when they arrive back to their families so that perhaps they will return again.´"
  12,63,"Then when they got back to their father´s house, they said, ´Father! Our measure will be denied. Please send our brother with us so we may obtain our measure. We will take care of him.´"